\title{direct sum of modules}
\taxon{definition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\cite{aluffi-2009}{Aluffi}{Section III.6.1}
\import{macros01}

\p{The \em{direct sum} #{M\oplus N} of two [#{R}-modules](rs-00B8) #{M} and #{N}
is the [biproduct](rs-00B2) in #{R}\scat{Mod}. Explicitly, the underlying
[abelian group](rs-007Y) is the [product](rs-009H), with #{R}-action
componentwise: ##{r(m, n) = (rm, rn).}} 
